## Success Criteria

The research passes if:
1. Every topic has a specific, differentiated angle — not the same as the title
2. Confidence scores have a clear justification in the rationale
3. Titles are concrete and specific (names specific technologies, products, or trends)
4. Suggested format matches the topic type (how-to topics get tutorial, not opinion)
5. Total found matches the actual count of topic objects

## Failure Criteria

Flag as failing if:
1. Topics are generic and could apply to any category
2. Angle is just the title rephrased as a sentence
3. Rationale is vague or missing
4. Confidence scores are all the same value
5. Topics exceed the requested count
